summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed from J. D. Weir, a bachelor, to The City of Seattle, dated March 17th, A. D. 1909, to all those certain tracts, lots or parcels of land, situated, lying and being in the County of King, State of Washington, particularly bounded and described as follows to-wit: Lots Three (3) and Four (4), Block Two (2), Ferry's Addition to Seattle, King County, Washington, according to the recorded plat thereof.
